cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a novel learning algorithm for online driver drowsiness estimation from EEG signals, which involves regression and domain adaptation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and computer vision (CV) aspects, which make cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) possible sub-categories as well.
